Member Function Documentation

virtual uint32 SubRouteList::addSubRoute (  RMSubRoute *  subRoute  )  [virtual]
 

Add a new SubRoute to this list.

If the route could be added, the subroute is owned by the list and should not be used anywhere else. I.e., if this function returns something else than MAX_UINT32, the subroute should be deleted.

Parameters:
subRoute The SubRoute that should be added to this list. Should never be used after a succesful adding to the list.
Returns:
The vector index of the added subroute, MAX_UINT32 upon failure.
